{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Adrian Beria Blog","author":"Adrian Beria"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"eeade01f-4d46-5dbd-a350-863afef4b2aa","excerpt":"Toolbar Lets continue with our Toolbar component, it will have a searchbar and a button to add games to the list. Searchbar Here is where…","html":"<h2>Toolbar</h2>\n<p>Lets continue with our Toolbar component, it will have a searchbar and a button to add games to the list.</p>\n<h3>Searchbar</h3>\n<p>Here is where things get interesting, we will have a case where we have two sibling components (Table and Toolbar) comunicating information to each other using a parent (MainPage), so on this case remember we can’t communicate upwards, so there are a few options we can use, one I tend to use are the callback functions.</p>\n<p>From the parent component you send a prop to Toolbar which is then read by Searchbar, the problem is we need to avoid prop drilling, and its reason we learned about React Context before taking on this part of the project. So lets set our Context!</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3a89373b62b019763710f0f4dee7e7cb/a4caf/redux-project-2.1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 477px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 35.84905660377359%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3a89373b62b019763710f0f4dee7e7cb/a4caf/redux-project-2.1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3a89373b62b019763710f0f4dee7e7cb/a2316/redux-project-2.1.png 148w,\n/static/3a89373b62b019763710f0f4dee7e7cb/8f18d/redux-project-2.1.png 295w,\n/static/3a89373b62b019763710f0f4dee7e7cb/a4caf/redux-project-2.1.png 477w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 477px) 100vw, 477px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>We add a utils folder and create a file with the name context.js where we put this code. We create our context ready to be used. Now lets set it up in the parent component which is in the page.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/699a9ba02c50474d93bc2e3979983d1f/56a1e/redux-project-2.2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 578px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 185.29411764705884%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/699a9ba02c50474d93bc2e3979983d1f/56a1e/redux-project-2.2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/699a9ba02c50474d93bc2e3979983d1f/8869e/redux-project-2.2.png 148w,\n/static/699a9ba02c50474d93bc2e3979983d1f/87a4d/redux-project-2.2.png 295w,\n/static/699a9ba02c50474d93bc2e3979983d1f/56a1e/redux-project-2.2.png 578w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 578px) 100vw, 578px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>We just added SearchProvider and surrounded Toolbar with it to send the callback function so we can get the value we put in the searchbar to search for our games, the value that the user puts will be read by MainPage and we use it to filter the value put there, notice we turn everything to lowercase to make it more efficent for the user.</p>\n<p>For the Searchbar it will look like this:</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/299fd19420870b02f3bf6e67913312a5/41d87/redux-project-2.3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 53.086419753086425%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/299fd19420870b02f3bf6e67913312a5/fb8a0/redux-project-2.3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/299fd19420870b02f3bf6e67913312a5/1a291/redux-project-2.3.png 148w,\n/static/299fd19420870b02f3bf6e67913312a5/2bc4a/redux-project-2.3.png 295w,\n/static/299fd19420870b02f3bf6e67913312a5/fb8a0/redux-project-2.3.png 590w,\n/static/299fd19420870b02f3bf6e67913312a5/41d87/redux-project-2.3.png 729w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>We import SearchContext and apply useContext with it as argument, so when we write anything on the input we activate an <strong>effect</strong> that triggers when the local state <strong>searchField</strong> gets modified, which is read by MainPage and we can filter the information we just read and send it as prop to the table.</p>\n<h3>Modal Component</h3>\n<h3>Forms</h3>\n<p>There are two common options for this part, <a href=\"https://github.com/final-form/react-final-form\">Final Form</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/jaredpalmer/formik\">Formik</a>, but since its a simple form we will do it the classic way which is relying on our </p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>See you on the next post.</p>\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\n<p><strong>Eng Adrian Beria.</strong></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Third Project - Redux - Part 2 Searchbar and Modal","date":"February 18, 2020"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/11-third-project-redux-part-2/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/7-Redux/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Redux"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/8-third-project-redux/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Third Project - Redux - Part 1 Fetch"}}}}